history.text: Hello how's it going?
Great how are you
Pretty good. What did you think of Iron Man?
I really liked the movie. I have seen it several times. What about you? What are your thoughts?
I've also seen it several times and so have a lot I can say about it. I always liked the "feel" they put into the movie with the music
Never thought about it from a director's standpoint. John Favreau is really talented
Yes he is. It is amazing what he is able to do with movies, especially in the Marvel franchise
And I really don't think any other actor than Robert Downey Jr. could have done even half as good a job
Yeah I don't know which all ones he's directed, but he kept Iron Man on track for sure
You are correct! Robert Downey did a great job!
I can't imagine anyone else being Tony Stark now
You're very right. Gweneth Paltrow was also great
All the cast of the first Iron Man movie were good actually, Terrence Howard was the best Rhody
Yeah Gwyneth Paltrow played her role really well. Probably more credit to the director thinking about it
What'd you think about the story line?
I thought it was great. The creation of the character and story as it unfolded was really well done
Yeah I agree the way Tony changed with the early plot was super
Being captured didn't completely change his persona but it developed it and inspired him to be Iron Man really nicely
That's right. It also showed off his genius and abilities which setup the rest of the movie and well
Do you think seeing it several times has made you look at the plot differently
I am not sure. It probably has, but each time I think I see the same things from the movie, but still love it
What about you?
I don't think the way I've looked at it has changed at all ever lol
it's just that good every single time
I agree with you there!
maybe Jeff Bridges seems more like a dick each time?
I think he plays the character well... At first I kinda liked him in an odd way in the role, then decided nah I didnt
His character is gets real evil really fast
Yes it does. What did you think of his solution to the arc reactor?
They probably could've changed stuff about his character actually to make the movie better. He was in the background more than he could have been
Which solution are we talking about
Where he tries to recreate the recator to create his own suits
Doesn't he end up taking Tony's reactor
Yeah he does...I do think his suit wasn't nearly as cool as the Iron Man suit
Again they probably could have developed his character a little more I think
Yes I agree
The arc reactor in general was super cool
Yes but it probably doesn't have any real scientific basis whatsoever lol
Anyway thanks for the conversation, and hope you see some good movies in the future!
You too!
